Brightening low-light images

Instructions are in the task pane to the left. Complete and submit each task one at a time.
This code sets up the activity.
bday = imread("./images/birthdayCake.jpeg");
imshow(bday)

Task 1

When an image is taken in low light conditions, you can brighten it using the imlocalbrighten function.
imgLight = imlocalbrighten(img);
This function works on both grayscale and color images.
bdayLight = imlocalbrighten(bday);
imshow(bdayLight)
